This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with language modeling using recurrent neural networks. Additionally, the use of LSTM units and word embeddings are common techniques in natural language processing, which is a subfield of CS.CL. 

The paper also involves the use of a gating mechanism, which is a common technique in deep learning and neural networks. This could place the paper in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Furthermore, the paper's focus on character-level inputs and word-level inputs could place it in the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), as these subfields often deal with image and text processing.
